textAnnotations.description:
YOUR MO
And there by the Scine was a bookshop, not the same, but similar to others I.
had known. An utrillo house, not too steady on its foundations, small windows,
wrinkled shutters. And there was George Whitman, undernourished, bearded, a
saint amongst his books, lending them, housing penniless friends upstairs, not
cager to sell, in the back of the store, in a small overcrowded room, with a
desk, a small stove.
(Anais Nin, Diary, Vol. 5)
